WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:13.760
The Wonderful Wizard of Oz by L. Frank Baum copyright black cat publishing

00:30.000 --> 00:47.600
Chapter 1 The Munchkins

00:47.600 --> 00:54.740
Dorothy lives in a small grey house in Kansas with her uncle Henry and M and little dog

00:55.740 --> 01:04.740
Everything in Kansas is grey. There are no trees or flowers, but there are cyclones.

01:04.740 --> 01:11.740
Cyclones are very strong winds. They can sometimes blow people and houses away.

01:11.740 --> 01:15.740
One day uncle Henry looks at the grey sky. He says,

01:15.740 --> 01:19.740
A cyclone is coming. We must go to the cellar.

01:19.740 --> 01:21.740
Come with us quickly Dorothy.

01:21.740 --> 01:27.740
This says Aunt Em. They run to the door of the cellar, but Toto is afraid.

01:27.740 --> 01:32.740
He runs into the bedroom and under the bed. Dorothy runs after him.

01:32.740 --> 01:35.740
Leave Toto and come to the cellar now!

01:35.740 --> 01:41.740
Cries Aunt Em. Dorothy picks Toto up and runs to the door of the cellar.

01:41.740 --> 01:47.740
But at that moment something strange happens.

01:47.740 --> 01:57.740
The cyclone is very strong and it picks the house up and takes it with Dorothy and Toto inside, into the sky.

01:57.740 --> 02:01.740
Uncle Henry and Aunt Em can only watch from the cellar.

02:01.740 --> 02:09.740
The house flies and flies in the sky for many hours. Dorothy and Toto are alone and afraid.

02:09.740 --> 02:15.740
After some time they become very tired and they fall asleep.

02:15.740 --> 02:22.740
When they wake up the house is on the ground.

02:22.740 --> 02:29.740
Everything is quiet. Dorothy opens the door quietly and goes out.

02:29.740 --> 02:36.740
It is a sunny day and she sees tall trees and beautiful flowers everywhere.

02:36.740 --> 02:38.740
This isn't Kansas Toto.

02:38.740 --> 02:39.740
Says Dorothy.

02:39.740 --> 02:43.740
Where are we and who are those people?

02:43.740 --> 02:47.740
Dorothy can see three short men and an old woman.

02:47.740 --> 02:53.740
The men are wearing blue hats, blue clothes and blue shoes.

02:53.740 --> 02:57.740
The old woman is wearing a beautiful white dress.

02:57.740 --> 03:00.740
She looks at Dorothy and says,

03:00.740 --> 03:03.740
We are very happy. You bring good luck.

03:03.740 --> 03:08.740
The wicked witch of the east is dead. The munchkins are her people.

03:08.740 --> 03:13.740
They are happy now because she is dead. Thank you dear girl.

03:13.740 --> 03:15.740
Dorothy is surprised.

03:15.740 --> 03:17.740
I don't understand.

03:17.740 --> 03:18.740
She says.

03:18.740 --> 03:21.740
The old woman and the munchkins smile at her.

03:21.740 --> 03:25.740
Look. The wicked witch of the east is under your house.

03:25.740 --> 03:27.740
Says the old woman.

03:27.740 --> 03:30.740
Look. You can see her feet.

03:30.740 --> 03:34.740
Dorothy sees two feet with silver shoes under her house.

03:34.740 --> 03:36.740
She jumps back in surprise.

03:36.740 --> 03:43.740
The old woman takes the silver shoes from the wicked witch's feet and gives them to Dorothy.

03:43.740 --> 03:50.740
They are your shoes now. You must wear them because a witch's shoes can do great things.

03:50.740 --> 03:52.740
But are you a witch too?

03:52.740 --> 03:53.740
Ask Dorothy.

03:53.740 --> 03:57.740
Yes. I'm the witch of the north. I'm a good witch.

03:57.740 --> 04:02.740
A good witch? I don't understand. Where are we?

04:02.740 --> 04:03.740
Says Dorothy.

04:03.740 --> 04:05.740
Where in the land of Oz?

04:05.740 --> 04:08.740
Here in the land of Oz there are four witches.

04:08.740 --> 04:10.740
Says the witch of the north.

04:10.740 --> 04:14.740
The witches of the north and south are very good witches.

04:14.740 --> 04:20.740
But the wicked witches of the east and the west are very bad witches.

04:20.740 --> 04:23.740
Now the wicked witch of the east is dead.

04:23.740 --> 04:28.740
There's only one wicked witch, the wicked witch of the west.

04:28.740 --> 04:31.740
Can you please help me go home to Kansas?

04:31.740 --> 04:32.740
Ask Dorothy.

04:32.740 --> 04:35.740
Kansas? Where's Kansas?

04:35.740 --> 04:36.740
Ask the good witch.

04:36.740 --> 04:39.740
I'm sorry, but I can't help you.

04:39.740 --> 04:43.740
You must go and see the Wizard of Oz in the Emerald City.

04:43.740 --> 04:46.740
He's a good wizard and he can help you.

04:46.740 --> 04:48.740
Where is the Emerald City?

04:48.740 --> 04:49.740
Ask Dorothy.

04:49.740 --> 04:52.740
It is far away. You must walk there.

04:52.740 --> 04:54.740
Says the good witch.

04:54.740 --> 04:56.740
Can you come with me?

04:56.740 --> 04:57.740
Ask Dorothy.

04:57.740 --> 05:01.740
No, I can't come with you, but I can give you my kiss.

05:01.740 --> 05:03.740
Says the good witch.

05:03.740 --> 05:06.740
She gives Dorothy a kiss on her forehead.

05:06.740 --> 05:11.740
Her kiss is special and looks like a little red flower.

05:11.740 --> 05:13.740
Now nothing can hurt you.

05:13.740 --> 05:15.740
Says the good witch.

05:15.740 --> 05:18.740
The yellow brick road goes to the Emerald City.

05:18.740 --> 05:21.740
Follow the yellow brick road.

05:21.740 --> 05:23.740
Goodbye, my dear.

05:23.740 --> 05:24.740
Goodbye.

05:24.740 --> 05:26.740
Says Dorothy.

05:26.740 --> 05:30.740
She goes to her house and puts some bread in a basket.

05:30.740 --> 05:35.740
Then she puts on a clean dress and the wicked witch's silver shoes.

05:35.740 --> 05:37.740
Let's go to the Emerald City, Toto.

05:37.740 --> 05:38.740
She says.

05:43.740 --> 05:46.740
Listening activity.

05:46.740 --> 05:50.740
Hello. My name is Scarecrow.

05:50.740 --> 05:53.740
I live in the land of the Munchkins.

05:53.740 --> 05:56.740
And I want to be your friend.

05:56.740 --> 06:03.740
I don't really like my job because I am very friendly and I don't like scaring the birds.

06:03.740 --> 06:08.740
I can't change jobs because I am not very clever.

06:08.740 --> 06:11.740
You see, I don't have a brain.

06:11.740 --> 06:16.740
I am going to the Emerald City to ask the Wizard of Oz for his help.

06:26.740 --> 06:30.740
Chapter 2. The Scarecrow.

06:37.740 --> 06:41.740
It is a sunny day in the land of the Munchkins.

06:41.740 --> 06:46.740
Dorothy and Toto walk along the yellow brick road all day.

06:46.740 --> 06:51.740
When Dorothy is tired, she sits down by the road near a Scarecrow.

06:51.740 --> 06:55.740
Suddenly, the Scarecrow smiles at her.

06:55.740 --> 06:57.740
She is very surprised.

06:57.740 --> 06:59.740
Can a Scarecrow smile?

06:59.740 --> 07:00.740
She thinks.

07:00.740 --> 07:02.740
Then the Scarecrow says.

07:02.740 --> 07:03.740
Hello.

07:03.740 --> 07:04.740
Oh.

07:04.740 --> 07:05.740
Says Dorothy.

07:05.740 --> 07:06.740
You can speak.

07:06.740 --> 07:08.740
Of course I can speak.

07:08.740 --> 07:09.740
Says the Scarecrow.

07:09.740 --> 07:11.740
But I can't move.

07:11.740 --> 07:13.740
Can you help me?

07:13.740 --> 07:16.740
Dorothy helps the Scarecrow to move from his post.

07:16.740 --> 07:18.740
Thank you very much.

07:18.740 --> 07:21.740
He says, moving his arms and legs.

07:21.740 --> 07:24.740
There's straw everywhere.

07:24.740 --> 07:25.740
Who are you?

07:25.740 --> 07:26.740
He asks.

07:26.740 --> 07:27.740
And where are you going?

07:27.740 --> 07:29.740
My name is Dorothy.

07:29.740 --> 07:31.740
I'm going to the Emerald City.

07:31.740 --> 07:33.740
I must find the Wizard of Oz.

07:33.740 --> 07:36.740
He can help me go back home to Kansas.

07:36.740 --> 07:38.740
Where is the Emerald City?

07:38.740 --> 07:39.740
He asks.

07:39.740 --> 07:41.740
And who is the Wizard of Oz?

07:41.740 --> 07:42.740
Don't you know?

07:42.740 --> 07:43.740
Ask Dorothy.

07:43.740 --> 07:44.740
No.

07:44.740 --> 07:46.740
I don't know anything.

07:46.740 --> 07:47.740
He says.

07:47.740 --> 07:49.740
I don't have a brain in my head.

07:49.740 --> 07:51.740
I only have straw.

07:51.740 --> 07:53.740
I'm very sorry.

07:53.740 --> 07:54.740
Says Dorothy.

07:54.740 --> 07:56.740
I want a brain.

07:56.740 --> 07:57.740
Says the Scarecrow.

07:57.740 --> 08:00.740
Can the Wizard of Oz give me a brain?

08:00.740 --> 08:01.740
I don't know.

08:01.740 --> 08:02.740
Says Dorothy.

08:02.740 --> 08:04.740
But you can come with me and ask him.

08:04.740 --> 08:05.740
Thank you.

08:05.740 --> 08:07.740
Says the Scarecrow.

08:07.740 --> 08:10.740
Toto looks at the Scarecrow and starts barking.

08:10.740 --> 08:12.740
Don't be afraid of Toto.

08:12.740 --> 08:13.740
He's a good dog.

08:13.740 --> 08:14.740
Says Dorothy.

08:14.740 --> 08:15.740
Oh.

08:15.740 --> 08:17.740
I'm not afraid of anything.

08:17.740 --> 08:18.740
Well.

08:18.740 --> 08:20.740
I am afraid of fire.

08:20.740 --> 08:21.740
Says the Scarecrow.

08:21.740 --> 08:23.740
Let me carry your basket.

08:23.740 --> 08:25.740
I never get tired.

08:25.740 --> 08:30.740
Dorothy, Toto and the Scarecrow walk along the yellow brick road.

08:30.740 --> 08:32.740
Soon, Dorothy is hungry.

08:32.740 --> 08:36.740
So she and Toto eat some bread from the basket.

08:36.740 --> 08:38.740
Do you want some bread, Scarecrow?

08:38.740 --> 08:39.740
Ask Dorothy.

08:39.740 --> 08:40.740
No thank you.

08:40.740 --> 08:41.740
He says.

08:41.740 --> 08:42.740
I'm never hungry.

08:42.740 --> 08:45.740
Please tell me about your home.

08:45.740 --> 08:47.740
Kansas is a dry, grey place.

08:47.740 --> 08:50.740
There are no trees and no flowers.

08:50.740 --> 08:53.740
There are cyclones every year.

08:53.740 --> 08:57.740
I live in a little house with my aunt M and uncle Henry.

08:57.740 --> 09:00.740
Why do you want to go back to Grey Kansas?

09:00.740 --> 09:02.740
Ask the Scarecrow.

09:02.740 --> 09:04.740
This country is very beautiful.

09:04.740 --> 09:07.740
There are a lot of trees and flowers.

09:07.740 --> 09:09.740
I don't understand.

09:09.740 --> 09:12.740
You don't understand because you don't have a brain.

09:12.740 --> 09:13.740
Says Dorothy.

09:13.740 --> 09:15.740
Kansas is my home.

09:15.740 --> 09:17.740
And I love my home.

09:18.740 --> 09:20.740
My aunt and uncle live there.

09:20.740 --> 09:23.740
The Scarecrow looks at her and smiles.

09:23.740 --> 09:26.740
Dorothy and Toto finish their bread.

09:26.740 --> 09:27.740
Well, let's go.

09:27.740 --> 09:28.740
Says Dorothy.

09:28.740 --> 09:31.740
The Emerald City is far away.

09:31.740 --> 09:34.740
In the evening, Dorothy is tired.

09:34.740 --> 09:37.740
They see a little house behind some trees.

09:37.740 --> 09:40.740
No one is in the house, so they go in.

09:40.740 --> 09:43.740
Dorothy and Toto sleep.

09:43.740 --> 09:45.740
But the Scarecrow doesn't.

09:45.740 --> 09:47.740
He laughs and says,

09:47.740 --> 09:55.740
Scarecrows don't sleep.

09:55.740 --> 09:57.740
Listening activity.

09:57.740 --> 10:00.740
So Scarecrow, is your job very boring?

10:00.740 --> 10:02.740
It's not boring at all.

10:02.740 --> 10:05.740
In fact, I do a lot of different things.

10:05.740 --> 10:07.740
Can you keep a secret?

10:07.740 --> 10:09.740
Yes, of course.

10:09.740 --> 10:11.740
So what do you do all day?

10:11.740 --> 10:14.740
Well, when the farmer leaves in the morning,

10:14.740 --> 10:18.740
I always wait for five minutes before I get off my post.

10:18.740 --> 10:22.740
I like reading about what is happening in the news.

10:22.740 --> 10:26.740
So I often read the farmer's newspaper, the Munchkin Times.

10:26.740 --> 10:31.740
After I finish the newspaper, I sometimes practice the violin.

10:31.740 --> 10:35.740
I am learning to play and I love it.

10:35.740 --> 10:38.740
It's such a beautiful musical instrument.

10:38.740 --> 10:43.740
Then in the afternoons, I usually go to see some of my friends in the area.

10:43.740 --> 10:46.740
There are lots of Scarecrows here, you know.

10:46.740 --> 10:47.740
How do you travel around?

10:47.740 --> 10:48.740
Do you drive?

10:48.740 --> 10:51.740
Oh no, I never drive.

10:51.740 --> 10:55.740
The farmer has a big tractor, but I don't like it.

10:55.740 --> 10:59.740
It's too noisy, and there's always a lot of smoke.

10:59.740 --> 11:01.740
I usually ride my bicycle.

11:01.740 --> 11:03.740
What do you and your friends usually do?

11:03.740 --> 11:08.740
Some of my friends like sports, so they often play tennis.

11:08.740 --> 11:12.740
I hardly ever play because I don't really like tennis.

11:12.740 --> 11:16.740
I usually play some card games with three or four friends.

11:16.740 --> 11:18.740
We can talk at the same time.

11:18.740 --> 11:21.740
What about when it is very hot and sunny?

11:21.740 --> 11:22.740
Do you sunbathe?

11:22.740 --> 11:28.740
But Dorothy, I never sunbathe because it is very dangerous for Scarecrows.

11:28.740 --> 11:33.740
I'm very afraid of it because I don't want to catch fire.

11:39.740 --> 11:40.740
Cyclones

11:41.740 --> 11:45.740
Sometimes very big storms become cyclones.

11:45.740 --> 11:50.740
Strong winds blow in opposite directions and make a shape like a funnel.

11:50.740 --> 11:56.740
When this powerful funnel touches the earth, it can blow everything away.

11:56.740 --> 11:59.740
People, animals, and even cars and houses.

11:59.740 --> 12:06.740
In the United States, there are approximately 1,000 reports of cyclones every year.

12:06.740 --> 12:08.740
But not all of these are dangerous.

12:08.740 --> 12:12.740
In fact, only about 10 to 20 are violent.

12:12.740 --> 12:21.740
Cyclones are very common in some of the central states, such as Texas, Oklahoma, Kansas, and Colorado.

12:21.740 --> 12:26.740
They usually happen between April and October because of the warm temperatures.

12:26.740 --> 12:36.740
On average, a cyclone lasts for about 15 to 20 minutes and can move from 75 miles, 131 kilometers,

12:36.740 --> 12:41.740
to 300 miles, 480 kilometers per hour.

12:41.740 --> 12:47.740
Some people are very interested in cyclones and like to follow them in their cars.

12:47.740 --> 12:52.740
Some are scientists, but some other people do this as a hobby.

12:52.740 --> 12:56.740
They write about each cyclone, take photos and make films.

12:56.740 --> 13:04.740
It is very dangerous, but it can help us understand more about what cyclones can do and why they happen.

13:06.740 --> 13:12.740
Listening activity

13:12.740 --> 13:15.740
Hello, I'm the Tin Woodman.

13:15.740 --> 13:19.740
I live in a little house in the forest.

13:19.740 --> 13:26.740
I have a tin body and I carry an axe because I cut down trees.

13:26.740 --> 13:33.740
I have an oil can too because I must put oil on my arms and legs.

13:33.740 --> 13:38.740
I'm sad because I don't love anyone.

13:41.740 --> 13:44.740
Hello, I'm the Lion.

13:44.740 --> 13:47.740
I live in the forest with other animals.

13:47.740 --> 13:51.740
I'm scary because I'm big.

13:51.740 --> 13:57.740
I have a big mouth, big teeth, and a long tail.

13:57.740 --> 14:02.740
I am very strong and can carry people on my back.

14:02.740 --> 14:10.740
I make a lot of noise, but I don't bite anyone because I'm afraid.

14:20.740 --> 14:31.740
Chapter 3. The Tin Woodman and the Lion

14:31.740 --> 14:37.740
The next morning, Dorothy and the Scarecrow hear a loud noise outside the house.

14:37.740 --> 14:38.740
What's that?

14:38.740 --> 14:39.740
Ask Dorothy.

14:39.740 --> 14:41.740
I don't know.

14:41.740 --> 14:42.740
Says the Scarecrow.

14:42.740 --> 14:44.740
Let's go and see.

14:44.740 --> 14:47.740
They run out of the house to the trees.

14:47.740 --> 14:50.740
They see a strange tin man by a tree.

14:50.740 --> 14:52.740
He has an axe in his hands.

14:52.740 --> 14:54.740
Help! Help!

14:54.740 --> 14:56.740
Cries the strange man.

14:56.740 --> 14:58.740
What's the matter?

14:58.740 --> 14:59.740
Ask Dorothy.

14:59.740 --> 15:00.740
I can't move.

15:00.740 --> 15:02.740
Says the Tin Woodman.

15:02.740 --> 15:06.740
Can you put some oil on my arms and legs, please?

15:06.740 --> 15:09.740
There's an oil can in my house.

15:09.740 --> 15:13.740
Dorothy runs back to the house and gets the oil can.

15:13.740 --> 15:18.740
She takes it to the Tin Woodman and they put some oil on his arms and legs.

15:18.740 --> 15:21.740
He slowly begins to move.

15:21.740 --> 15:26.740
First, he moves his head, then his arms and legs.

15:26.740 --> 15:27.740
Thank you.

15:27.740 --> 15:30.740
He says, I feel better now.

15:30.740 --> 15:33.740
Sometimes I get wet in the rain.

15:33.740 --> 15:37.740
Water is very bad for my tin body.

15:37.740 --> 15:39.740
Who are you?

15:39.740 --> 15:41.740
And where are you going?

15:41.740 --> 15:44.740
I'm Dorothy and this is the Scarecrow.

15:44.740 --> 15:50.740
We're going to the Emerald City to find the Wizard of Oz because he can help me go back to Kansas.

15:50.740 --> 15:53.740
Perhaps he can also give the Scarecrow a brain.

15:53.740 --> 15:56.740
Can the Wizard of Oz give me a heart?

15:56.740 --> 15:58.740
Asks the Tin Woodman.

15:58.740 --> 16:03.740
I don't have a heart and I can't love anyone.

16:03.740 --> 16:06.740
There is no happiness without love.

16:06.740 --> 16:08.740
Why don't you come with us?

16:08.740 --> 16:09.740
Says the Scarecrow.

16:09.740 --> 16:10.740
Yes.

16:10.740 --> 16:12.740
You can ask the Wizard for a heart.

16:12.740 --> 16:13.740
Says Dorothy.

16:13.740 --> 16:15.740
Thank you, my friends.

16:15.740 --> 16:17.740
Says the Tin Woodman.

16:17.740 --> 16:19.740
And they start walking again.

16:20.740 --> 16:24.740
The three friends in Toto walk along the yellow brick road.

16:24.740 --> 16:27.740
They look at all the tall trees near the road.

16:27.740 --> 16:32.740
There are a lot of noises coming from the different animals behind the trees.

16:32.740 --> 16:36.740
Suddenly, a lion jumps out into the road.

16:36.740 --> 16:39.740
He opens his big mouth and roars.

16:45.740 --> 16:48.740
He has big teeth and wants to bite Toto.

16:48.740 --> 16:54.740
Dorothy is afraid for Toto and she runs to the lion and hits him on the nose with her basket.

16:54.740 --> 16:56.740
Don't hurt my dog.

16:56.740 --> 16:57.740
She cries angrily.

16:57.740 --> 16:59.740
He's small and you're big.

16:59.740 --> 17:01.740
Don't hit me, please.

17:01.740 --> 17:03.740
Says the lion.

17:03.740 --> 17:05.740
You're afraid.

17:05.740 --> 17:06.740
Says Dorothy.

17:06.740 --> 17:08.740
You're a lion and you're afraid.

17:08.740 --> 17:10.740
You're a coward.

17:10.740 --> 17:12.740
Yes, I am a coward.

17:12.740 --> 17:16.740
Lions must be courageous, but I'm not.

17:16.740 --> 17:19.740
I make a lot of noise, but I am a coward.

17:19.740 --> 17:23.740
Says the lion sadly as he starts crying.

17:23.740 --> 17:26.740
Don't cry.

17:26.740 --> 17:27.740
Says Dorothy.

17:27.740 --> 17:30.740
Come with us to the Emerald City.

17:30.740 --> 17:33.740
Perhaps the Wizard of Oz can give you courage.

17:33.740 --> 17:38.740
So they all continue walking along the yellow brick road.

17:38.740 --> 17:41.740
At one point, they see a big river.

17:41.740 --> 17:43.740
How can we cross the river?

17:43.740 --> 17:44.740
Ask Dorothy.

17:44.740 --> 17:50.740
The lion looks at the river and says, I can jump across, but I'm afraid.

17:50.740 --> 17:52.740
Don't be afraid.

17:52.740 --> 17:53.740
Says the Scarecrow.

17:53.740 --> 17:55.740
You're a strong lion.

17:55.740 --> 17:58.740
You can take us on your back one by one.

17:58.740 --> 18:00.740
Oh, all right.

18:00.740 --> 18:01.740
I can do that.

18:01.740 --> 18:02.740
Says the lion.

18:02.740 --> 18:08.740
You don't have a brain, but you have good ideas, Scarecrow.

18:08.740 --> 18:11.740
And so the lion jumps across the river.

18:11.740 --> 18:15.740
He takes the Scarecrow first and then he takes Dorothy in total.

18:15.740 --> 18:21.740
He takes the Tin Woodman last.

18:21.740 --> 18:27.740
Listening activity.

18:27.740 --> 18:29.740
Where do lions live?

18:29.740 --> 18:33.740
Most lions today live in parts of Africa.

18:33.740 --> 18:37.740
Lions like areas with lots of grass.

18:37.740 --> 18:40.740
How many lions are there in the world?

18:40.740 --> 18:45.080
Today there are about 20,000 lions in Africa.

18:45.080 --> 18:46.840
How long do they live?

18:46.840 --> 18:51.240
In captivity, lions can live for about 25 years.

18:51.240 --> 18:56.420
In the wild, they usually only live for about 8 to 10 years.

18:56.420 --> 18:57.920
How do they live?

18:57.920 --> 19:02.760
Lions are social animals, and they live in groups called a pride.

19:02.760 --> 19:07.000
Some prides are very small, and some are very big.

19:07.000 --> 19:10.700
Most have about 15 lions.

19:10.700 --> 19:14.240
What differences are there between males and females?

19:14.240 --> 19:18.940
Male lions have long hair around their face, called a mane.

19:18.940 --> 19:23.940
Male lions protect the pride when the female lions look for food.

19:23.940 --> 19:25.520
How big are they?

19:25.520 --> 19:33.060
An adult male can be about 2 meters long, and can weigh from 170 to 230 kilograms.

19:33.060 --> 19:43.400
An adult female is smaller, and about 1.5 meters long, and with a weight of about 120 to 180 kilograms.

19:43.400 --> 19:45.400
How often do they have cubs?

19:45.400 --> 19:53.940
Lions in captivity can have cubs every year, but lions in the wild usually have cubs only every two years.

19:53.940 --> 19:58.280
The lioness can have from 1 to 6 cubs at a time.

20:03.060 --> 20:18.400
Chapter 4 The Emerald City

20:18.400 --> 20:21.360
The four friends walk all day.

20:21.360 --> 20:26.640
In the evening, they see some little green houses and some little people in green clothes.

20:26.640 --> 20:29.400
Everything's green, says Dorothy.

20:29.400 --> 20:31.640
We're near the Emerald City.

20:31.640 --> 20:34.860
Soon they come to a big green door.

20:34.860 --> 20:42.020
It opens slowly, and they see a little man in green clothes and green glasses.

20:42.020 --> 20:45.900
We want to see the Wizard of Oz, please, says Dorothy.

20:45.900 --> 20:48.900
Okay, follow me, says the little man.

20:48.900 --> 20:51.380
But first, put these on.

20:51.380 --> 20:57.860
He opens a big box, and inside there are lots of piers of green glasses.

20:57.860 --> 21:00.180
You must wear these glasses.

21:00.200 --> 21:07.920
Everybody in the Emerald City wears them, so they put on the glasses and go into the Emerald City.

21:07.920 --> 21:11.400
They stop in front of the Palace of Oz.

21:11.400 --> 21:13.480
A man opens the door.

21:13.480 --> 21:16.120
Follow me, he says.

21:16.120 --> 21:19.400
He takes them into a big green room.

21:19.400 --> 21:22.240
Now, wait here until I call you.

21:22.240 --> 21:24.360
When he returns, he says,

21:24.360 --> 21:27.240
The Wizard wants to see the girl first.

21:27.240 --> 21:30.500
But Dorothy goes into a beautiful room.

21:30.500 --> 21:37.620
On a green chair, there is only a very big head without a body, arms, or legs.

21:37.620 --> 21:40.420
She is surprised and afraid.

21:40.420 --> 21:43.820
I am Oz, says the big head.

21:43.820 --> 21:46.620
Who are you and what do you want?

21:46.620 --> 21:50.180
I'm Dorothy, and I want to go home to Kansas.

21:50.180 --> 21:51.980
I don't know the way.

21:51.980 --> 21:54.220
Can you help me, please?

21:54.220 --> 22:00.040
The big eyes open and close, then the mouth opens and speaks.

22:00.040 --> 22:06.480
Perhaps I can help you, but first, you must kill the wicked witch of the West.

22:06.480 --> 22:08.680
Oh no, says Dorothy.

22:08.680 --> 22:10.920
I don't want to kill anyone.

22:10.920 --> 22:13.960
The wicked witch of the East is dead.

22:13.960 --> 22:17.360
You are wearing her silver shoes.

22:17.360 --> 22:21.840
Now, go and kill the wicked witch of the West.

22:21.840 --> 22:25.020
How can I kill the wicked witch of the West?

22:25.020 --> 22:27.780
She asks, where is she?

22:27.780 --> 22:30.820
The head does not answer.

22:30.820 --> 22:34.860
Dorothy leaves the room, and the scarecrow goes in.

22:34.860 --> 22:37.900
But the scarecrow does not see a big head.

22:37.900 --> 22:40.820
He sees a beautiful woman.

22:40.820 --> 22:46.740
Oh, great Oz, please give me a brain, says the scarecrow.

22:46.740 --> 22:51.620
First, you must kill the wicked witch of the West.

22:51.620 --> 22:56.680
It says Oz, the tin woodman enters the green room.

22:56.680 --> 23:03.880
He sees an ugly monster with five eyes, five arms, and five legs.

23:03.880 --> 23:08.440
Oh, great Oz, please give me a heart, says the tin woodman.

23:08.440 --> 23:14.160
First, you must help Dorothy and the scarecrow kill the wicked witch of the West.

23:14.160 --> 23:20.720
Says Oz, the tin woodman leaves the room, and the lion goes in.

23:20.720 --> 23:23.860
He sees a big ball of fire.

23:23.860 --> 23:24.860
He is afraid.

23:24.860 --> 23:29.100
Oh, great Oz, please give me courage.

23:29.100 --> 23:30.100
Says the lion.

23:30.100 --> 23:37.220
I can only give you courage when the wicked witch of the West is dead.

23:37.220 --> 23:41.100
When the friends meet, they talk about the strange wizard.

23:41.100 --> 23:44.780
Now we must find the wicked witch of the West and kill her.

23:44.780 --> 23:45.780
Says Dorothy.

23:45.780 --> 23:47.220
Yes, we must.

23:47.220 --> 23:49.620
They all say.

23:49.620 --> 23:54.360
The friends leave the Emerald City to find the wicked witch of the West.

23:54.360 --> 23:59.520
On their way out, they give their glasses to the little man at the gate.

23:59.520 --> 24:02.880
Dorothy asks him, where is the wicked witch of the West?

24:02.880 --> 24:04.280
We must find her.

24:04.280 --> 24:07.160
She lives in the land of the wing keys.

24:07.160 --> 24:09.960
He says, you must walk to the West.

24:09.960 --> 24:11.320
Be careful.

24:11.320 --> 24:16.280
She is very bad, and everyone is afraid of her.

24:16.280 --> 24:23.560
So Dorothy, the scarecrow, the tin woodman, the lion and todo, start walking to the West.

24:23.560 --> 24:27.020
They walk for a long time.

24:27.020 --> 24:32.280
Above them in her castle, the wicked witch of the West watches them.

24:32.280 --> 24:36.280
The wicked witch has a magic eye and can see everything.

24:36.280 --> 24:39.240
Who are those people on my road?

24:39.240 --> 24:52.680
She says angrily.

24:52.680 --> 25:06.520
Chapter 5 The Wicked Witch of the West

25:06.520 --> 25:13.040
The witch blows her silver whistle, and forty winged monkeys quickly arrive.

25:13.040 --> 25:14.040
What do you want?

25:14.040 --> 25:16.400
The king of the winged monkeys asks.

25:16.400 --> 25:20.440
There are three people, a dog and a lion on my road.

25:20.440 --> 25:26.120
She says, go and kill the people and the dog, but bring me the lion.

25:26.120 --> 25:28.600
He is big and strong.

25:28.600 --> 25:30.080
He can work for me.

25:30.080 --> 25:32.080
Yes, immediately.

25:32.080 --> 25:36.240
Say the winged monkeys, and they fly away.

25:36.240 --> 25:40.800
They quickly reach the road and see the four friends and the dog.

25:40.800 --> 25:43.920
They break the tin woodman's arms and legs.

25:43.920 --> 25:48.720
They take the straw out of the scarecrow and throw his clothes into a tree.

25:48.720 --> 25:52.200
Then they take the lion to the wicked witch's castle.

25:52.200 --> 25:57.560
The winged monkeys do not hurt Dorothy in toto because they see the good witch's kiss

25:57.560 --> 25:59.760
on Dorothy's forehead.

25:59.760 --> 26:04.760
They decide to take them to the wicked witch's castle with the lion.

26:04.760 --> 26:11.320
The wicked witch sees the kiss on Dorothy's face and she is afraid, but she doesn't say

26:11.320 --> 26:12.320
anything.

26:12.320 --> 26:13.320
Ha ha!

26:13.320 --> 26:15.360
Now you are my prisoner.

26:15.360 --> 26:20.760
You must work in my house every day, clean this dirty kitchen.

26:20.760 --> 26:27.040
She says to Dorothy, remember I can watch you all the time.

26:27.040 --> 26:30.880
Dorothy looks at her sadly and starts to clean the kitchen.

26:30.880 --> 26:33.520
How can I go back to Kansas now?

26:33.520 --> 26:35.000
She thinks.

26:35.000 --> 26:37.960
She is very unhappy.

26:37.960 --> 26:45.240
Dorothy does not know her shoes are magic, but the wicked witch knows and she wants them.

26:45.240 --> 26:48.440
One morning Dorothy's left shoe falls off.

26:48.440 --> 26:53.440
The wicked witch quickly takes it and says, This is my shoe now.

26:53.440 --> 26:54.640
No it isn't.

26:54.640 --> 26:57.680
Christ Dorothy angrily, Give it to me.

26:57.680 --> 27:02.000
The wicked witch then tries to take the other shoe too.

27:02.000 --> 27:05.960
Dorothy is very angry because she loves her silver shoes.

27:05.960 --> 27:08.920
She sees a bucket of water near the door.

27:08.920 --> 27:12.200
She takes it and throws the water at the wicked witch.

27:12.200 --> 27:13.200
No!

27:13.200 --> 27:14.800
Don't do that!

27:14.800 --> 27:17.400
cries the wicked witch of the west.

27:17.400 --> 27:19.400
Water kills me!

27:19.400 --> 27:20.400
Help!

27:20.400 --> 27:24.800
Help me please!

27:24.800 --> 27:31.480
Now on the floor, there is only the wicked witch's black hat, her black dress, and her

27:31.480 --> 27:34.040
silver whistle.

27:34.040 --> 27:37.600
Dorothy looks for her but cannot find her.

27:37.600 --> 27:39.600
She puts her left shoe on again.

27:39.600 --> 27:43.320
Now I am free and I can help my friends.

27:43.320 --> 27:46.840
Dorothy says, Perhaps I can call the winged monkeys.

27:46.840 --> 27:50.280
She picks up the witch's silver whistle and looks at it.

27:50.280 --> 27:51.840
Is this a magic whistle?

27:51.840 --> 27:53.320
She thinks.

27:53.320 --> 27:55.880
She blows it.

27:55.880 --> 27:58.160
And the winged monkeys arrive.

27:58.160 --> 28:00.600
She is surprised and happy.

28:00.600 --> 28:02.720
Can you help my friends?

28:02.720 --> 28:03.720
She asks.

28:03.720 --> 28:04.720
Yes!

28:04.720 --> 28:05.800
Says one monkey.

28:05.800 --> 28:20.960
We always help the person with the magic whistle.

28:20.960 --> 28:30.800
Number six, back to the Emerald City.

28:30.800 --> 28:34.400
The winged monkeys find a lion and free him.

28:34.400 --> 28:36.320
He is happy now.

28:36.320 --> 28:40.480
They find the scarecrow's clothes and puts them straw in them.

28:40.480 --> 28:45.080
The scarecrow laughs and says, Thank you!

28:45.080 --> 28:47.920
Then the winged monkeys help the tin woodman.

28:47.920 --> 28:50.320
They give him a new oil can.

28:50.320 --> 28:53.240
So I can move my arms and legs.

28:53.240 --> 28:54.240
Thank you!

28:54.240 --> 28:55.240
He says.

28:55.240 --> 28:57.120
The wicked witch of the West is dead.

28:57.120 --> 28:59.840
Says Dorothy to her friends.

28:59.840 --> 29:01.560
Everyone is very happy.

29:01.560 --> 29:04.640
We must go back to the Wizard of Oz and tell him.

29:04.640 --> 29:05.640
Says Dorothy.

29:05.640 --> 29:08.200
The winged monkeys can take us back to the Emerald City.

29:08.200 --> 29:09.840
Blow the magic whistle.

29:09.840 --> 29:12.200
Says the tin woodman.

29:12.200 --> 29:14.880
Dorothy blows the whistle.

29:14.880 --> 29:16.960
And the monkeys come again.

29:16.960 --> 29:20.480
They carry Dorothy and her friends up into the sky.

29:20.480 --> 29:24.240
Soon they are at the green door of the Emerald City.

29:24.240 --> 29:27.200
The little green man opens the door.

29:27.200 --> 29:31.320
He gives them glasses and takes them to the palace.

29:31.320 --> 29:36.160
They go to the Wizard's room, but no one is there.

29:36.160 --> 29:40.320
A voice says, I am the Wizard of Oz!

29:40.320 --> 29:41.520
Where are you?

29:41.520 --> 29:42.520
asks Dorothy.

29:42.520 --> 29:46.480
I am everywhere, but you can't see me.

29:46.480 --> 29:47.480
Says the Wizard.

29:47.480 --> 29:48.480
Who are you?

29:48.480 --> 29:49.840
And what do you want?

29:49.840 --> 29:51.560
Don't you remember us?

29:51.560 --> 29:52.880
I am Dorothy.

29:52.880 --> 29:57.600
I am here with my friends, the scarecrow, the tin woodman, and the lion.

29:57.600 --> 30:02.000
The wicked witch of the West is dead, and you must keep your promise.

30:02.000 --> 30:04.080
I want to go home to Kansas.

30:04.080 --> 30:06.240
Yes, says the scarecrow.

30:06.240 --> 30:10.240
The wicked witch is dead, so you must give me a brain.

30:10.240 --> 30:12.400
And you must give me a heart.

30:12.400 --> 30:13.760
Says the tin woodman.

30:13.760 --> 30:16.000
And I want some courage.

30:16.000 --> 30:17.000
Says the lion.

30:17.000 --> 30:21.400
Is the wicked witch of the West really dead?

30:21.400 --> 30:22.400
asks the Wizard.

30:22.400 --> 30:23.880
Yes, she is.

30:23.880 --> 30:27.280
They all say, come back tomorrow.

30:27.280 --> 30:28.280
Says the Wizard.

30:28.280 --> 30:30.880
I must think about this.

30:30.880 --> 30:34.680
No, I don't want to come back tomorrow.

30:34.680 --> 30:35.680
Says the tin woodman.

30:35.680 --> 30:37.880
I want a heart now.

30:37.880 --> 30:40.160
And I want a brain now.

30:40.160 --> 30:41.160
Says the scarecrow.

30:41.160 --> 30:44.920
I am angry, and I am going to eat you.

30:44.920 --> 30:46.080
Says the lion.

30:46.080 --> 30:48.920
He opens his big mouth and roars.

30:48.920 --> 30:49.920
Roar.

30:49.920 --> 30:55.040
Toto, afraid of the lion, jumps up and hits a big screen.

30:55.040 --> 31:00.960
It falls over.

31:00.960 --> 31:06.080
And the friends see a little old man with no hair.

31:06.080 --> 31:08.360
They are very surprised.

31:08.360 --> 31:11.160
The tin woodman is angry and picks up his axe.

31:11.160 --> 31:12.760
Who are you?

31:12.760 --> 31:13.760
Says the tin woodman.

31:13.760 --> 31:14.760
I am Ozz.

31:14.760 --> 31:15.760
Look great.

31:15.760 --> 31:20.200
Says the little man in a quiet voice.

31:20.200 --> 31:22.280
Oh, please don't hurt me.

31:22.280 --> 31:25.160
But the Wizard is a big head with no body.

31:25.160 --> 31:26.160
Says Dorothy.

31:26.160 --> 31:27.160
No.

31:27.160 --> 31:28.880
It's a beautiful woman.

31:28.880 --> 31:29.880
Says the scarecrow.

31:29.880 --> 31:30.880
You're wrong.

31:30.880 --> 31:35.840
It's a monster with five eyes, five arms, and five legs.

31:35.840 --> 31:37.040
Says the tin woodman.

31:37.040 --> 31:38.040
No.

31:38.040 --> 31:39.040
Says the lion.

31:39.040 --> 31:42.480
The Wizard is a big ball of fire.

31:42.480 --> 31:45.600
You're all wrong, says the little man quietly.

31:45.600 --> 31:49.520
I am the wizard, but I'm not a real wizard.

31:49.520 --> 31:51.760
I'm from Kansas, too.

31:51.760 --> 31:55.200
I like traveling in hot air balloons.

31:55.200 --> 31:56.880
That is why I'm here.

31:56.880 --> 31:58.360
Oh.

31:58.360 --> 32:02.200
Say the four friends, and they look at each other.

32:02.200 --> 32:08.120
The people here think I'm a wizard because I come from the sky, says the little man.

32:08.120 --> 32:12.160
I live inside this palace and never go out.

32:12.160 --> 32:13.960
No one must see me.

32:13.960 --> 32:16.400
Everyone must think I'm a real wizard.

32:16.400 --> 32:21.640
The scarecrow takes off his glasses and says, The Emerald City isn't green.

32:21.640 --> 32:27.680
It just looks green because everyone wears green glasses.

32:27.680 --> 32:29.840
It's a trick.

32:29.840 --> 32:31.480
Everything here is a trick.

32:31.480 --> 32:33.280
Yes, it's a trick.

32:33.280 --> 32:34.840
Says the little man sadly.

32:34.840 --> 32:40.920
I'm very sorry, but I don't know any magic, so I can't help you.

32:40.920 --> 32:42.560
You're a bad man.

32:42.560 --> 32:43.560
Says Dorothy.

32:43.560 --> 32:49.000
No, I'm a good man, but I am a very bad wizard.

32:49.000 --> 32:53.800
He says, Now the wicked witch of the west is dead, says the scarecrow.

32:53.800 --> 32:55.760
You must keep your promise.

32:55.760 --> 32:57.880
I want a brain.

32:57.880 --> 32:58.880
You're right.

32:58.880 --> 32:59.880
Says Oz.

32:59.880 --> 33:02.360
I must keep my promise.

33:02.360 --> 33:08.480
Come back tomorrow.

33:08.480 --> 33:11.160
Learning activity.

33:11.160 --> 33:12.160
One.

33:12.160 --> 33:15.360
Dear Great Oz, please tell me.

33:15.360 --> 33:17.800
How can I make a very big head?

33:17.800 --> 33:22.040
First, you must use lots and lots of paper.

33:22.040 --> 33:26.800
And with some water, you can make a very big ball.

33:26.800 --> 33:28.200
Two.

33:28.200 --> 33:31.840
How do you make the face?

33:31.840 --> 33:37.960
Well, you paint separate pieces of paper and you put them in the correct places.

33:38.960 --> 33:40.960
Three.

33:40.960 --> 33:44.320
How do the eyes and the mouth move?

33:44.320 --> 33:51.800
Well, you use string or some cord or cotton to pull the eyes and the mouth.

33:51.800 --> 33:55.560
I sit on the balcony and do this.

33:55.560 --> 33:57.040
Four.

33:57.040 --> 34:01.400
What do you do to make the head speak?

34:01.400 --> 34:07.840
Ah, you see, I am not a wizard, but I am a ventriloquist.

34:07.840 --> 34:13.280
This means I can speak from one side of the room, but the sound can come from the

34:13.280 --> 34:22.800
place where the head is.

34:22.800 --> 34:41.560
The next morning, the four friends go to the wizard's room.

34:41.560 --> 34:44.720
The scarecrow asks, is my brain ready?

34:44.720 --> 34:46.560
Please, sit down.

34:46.560 --> 34:47.560
Says Oz.

34:47.560 --> 34:50.400
First, I must open your head.

34:50.400 --> 34:53.280
Then I can put your brain in the right place.

34:53.280 --> 34:55.680
Now, don't move.

34:55.680 --> 35:00.640
The little man opens a green box with the word brain on it.

35:00.640 --> 35:04.240
He slowly puts a brain into the scarecrow's head.

35:04.240 --> 35:06.840
Now, you have a brain.

35:06.840 --> 35:09.600
You are a very clever scarecrow.

35:09.600 --> 35:10.600
Says Oz.

35:10.600 --> 35:12.240
Oh, thank you.

35:12.240 --> 35:13.400
Says the scarecrow.

35:13.400 --> 35:16.160
I finally have a brain.

35:16.160 --> 35:18.120
The tin woodman is next.

35:18.120 --> 35:19.320
He is excited.

35:19.320 --> 35:20.500
Where is my heart?

35:20.500 --> 35:22.200
He asks.

35:22.200 --> 35:28.480
Oz goes to a big green box and takes out a beautiful red heart.

35:28.480 --> 35:31.640
Here is a special red heart.

35:31.640 --> 35:33.720
Wear it all the time.

35:33.720 --> 35:34.720
Says Oz.

35:34.720 --> 35:37.080
Is it a kind heart?

35:37.080 --> 35:38.360
Asks the tin woodman.

35:38.360 --> 35:41.600
Yes, it's a very kind heart.

35:41.600 --> 35:42.600
Says Oz.

35:42.600 --> 35:44.480
I'm very happy.

35:44.480 --> 35:45.480
Thank you.

35:45.480 --> 35:46.760
Says the tin woodman.

35:46.920 --> 35:50.120
Now, I can love someone.

35:50.120 --> 35:53.080
Now, you must give me courage.

35:53.080 --> 35:54.640
Says the lion.

35:54.640 --> 35:59.080
Oz gives him a green bottle with the word courage on it.

35:59.080 --> 36:02.280
Drink this, he says to the lion.

36:02.280 --> 36:05.960
The lion drinks it quickly and then smiles.

36:05.960 --> 36:10.320
Now, I feel courageous, very courageous.

36:10.320 --> 36:11.440
Says the lion.

36:11.440 --> 36:13.360
Thank you.

36:13.360 --> 36:15.560
And what about Toto and me?

36:15.560 --> 36:17.560
Asks Dorothy quietly.

36:17.560 --> 36:20.640
I can take you to Kansas in my hot air balloon.

36:20.640 --> 36:21.680
Says Oz.

36:21.680 --> 36:23.800
Come with me.

36:23.800 --> 36:27.560
They go into his garden and see the big hot air balloon

36:27.560 --> 36:30.120
with a small box under it.

36:30.120 --> 36:33.840
Oz gets into the box and says, come on, Dorothy.

36:33.840 --> 36:36.320
We're going to Kansas.

36:36.320 --> 36:40.520
Dorothy says goodbye to the scarecrow, the tin woodman,

36:40.520 --> 36:41.520
and the lion.

36:41.520 --> 36:42.680
Come on, Toto.

36:42.680 --> 36:44.640
We're going home to Kansas.

36:44.640 --> 36:48.120
But Toto suddenly sees a cat and runs after it.

36:48.120 --> 36:49.920
Toto, come here.

36:49.920 --> 36:51.240
Says Dorothy.

36:51.240 --> 36:52.840
She runs after Toto.

36:52.840 --> 36:55.600
Dorothy, the rope is breaking.

36:55.600 --> 36:56.600
Says the wizard.

36:56.600 --> 36:57.840
Come quickly.

36:57.840 --> 37:01.840
Dorothy picks up Toto and runs to the hot air balloon.

37:01.840 --> 37:05.200
But the rope breaks and the big hot air balloon

37:05.200 --> 37:07.120
goes up into the sky.

37:07.120 --> 37:10.320
Go to the land of the quadlings.

37:10.320 --> 37:11.440
Cries the wizard.

37:11.440 --> 37:15.040
The good witch of the south lives there.

37:15.040 --> 37:17.160
She can help you.

37:17.160 --> 37:19.080
Goodbye.

37:19.080 --> 37:21.240
The hot air balloon and the wizard

37:21.240 --> 37:23.800
disappear into the sky forever.

37:29.080 --> 37:29.580
Yay!

37:29.580 --> 37:30.080
Yay!

37:31.080 --> 37:39.280
Chapter 8, the good witch of the south.

37:47.880 --> 37:49.960
How can I go home now?

37:49.960 --> 37:51.680
Dorothy asks sadly.

37:51.680 --> 37:54.320
Where's the land of the quadlings?

37:54.320 --> 37:58.200
And who is the good witch of the south?

37:58.200 --> 38:00.280
She starts crying.

38:00.280 --> 38:03.160
The tin woodman looks at her and starts crying too.

38:03.160 --> 38:04.520
Don't cry.

38:04.520 --> 38:05.880
Says the scarecrow.

38:05.880 --> 38:09.280
Water is bad for your tin body.

38:09.280 --> 38:11.320
Blow the magic whistle, Dorothy.

38:11.320 --> 38:12.640
Says the scarecrow.

38:12.640 --> 38:14.720
The winged monkeys can help you.

38:14.720 --> 38:16.680
You're a clever scarecrow.

38:16.680 --> 38:18.200
Says Dorothy.

38:18.200 --> 38:21.960
She blows the magic whistle.

38:21.960 --> 38:24.200
And the winged monkeys arrive.

38:24.200 --> 38:26.680
Please take us to the land of the quadlings.

38:26.680 --> 38:27.560
She says.

38:27.560 --> 38:30.560
I must find the good witch of the south.

38:30.560 --> 38:33.040
The winged monkeys take Dorothy and her friends

38:33.040 --> 38:35.360
to the land of the quadlings.

38:35.360 --> 38:38.480
The land of the quadlings is lovely.

38:38.480 --> 38:41.600
There are flowers and trees everywhere.

38:41.600 --> 38:43.760
All the houses are red.

38:43.760 --> 38:47.400
The quadlings are short and they all wear red clothes

38:47.400 --> 38:49.160
and red shoes.

38:49.160 --> 38:52.560
A kind quadling woman gives them some cake and milk.

38:52.560 --> 38:54.200
Where is the castle, please?

38:54.200 --> 38:55.280
Ask Dorothy.

38:55.280 --> 38:57.520
Take the road to the south.

38:57.520 --> 38:59.760
Says the kind woman.

38:59.760 --> 39:02.560
When the friends arrive at the beautiful castle,

39:02.560 --> 39:06.200
they see three quadling girls outside the castle gate.

39:06.200 --> 39:07.520
Why are you here?

39:07.520 --> 39:09.920
Asks one girl in a friendly voice.

39:09.920 --> 39:12.280
I want to see the good witch of the south.

39:12.280 --> 39:13.400
Says Dorothy.

39:13.400 --> 39:14.880
Please wait here.

39:14.880 --> 39:16.760
Says the other girl.

39:16.760 --> 39:20.280
After a few minutes, the three girls return and say.

39:20.280 --> 39:22.200
Follow us, please.

39:22.200 --> 39:25.840
Soon, Dorothy and her friends enter a big room

39:25.840 --> 39:28.360
and see the good witch of the south.

39:28.360 --> 39:30.960
She is young and beautiful.

39:30.960 --> 39:33.680
She has red hair and blue eyes.

39:33.680 --> 39:36.520
She is wearing a long white dress.

39:36.520 --> 39:39.280
What can I do for you, my child?

39:39.280 --> 39:40.600
Asks the good witch.

39:40.600 --> 39:42.720
I want to go home to Kansas.

39:42.720 --> 39:43.760
Says Dorothy.

39:43.760 --> 39:45.200
Can you help me?

39:45.200 --> 39:48.880
She looks at Dorothy's silver shoes and smiles.

39:48.880 --> 39:51.160
Your silver shoes are magic.

39:51.160 --> 39:52.160
She says.

39:52.160 --> 39:54.320
They can take you home.

39:54.320 --> 39:56.520
First, close your eyes.

39:56.520 --> 40:00.160
Then click your heels three times and say,

40:00.160 --> 40:02.880
take me home to Kansas.

40:02.880 --> 40:03.960
That's easy.

40:03.960 --> 40:05.400
Says Dorothy happily.

40:05.400 --> 40:06.760
Thank you.

40:06.760 --> 40:08.440
And what about your friends?

40:08.440 --> 40:09.600
Says the good witch.

40:09.600 --> 40:11.400
What do they want?

40:11.400 --> 40:13.440
I'm a clever scarecrow.

40:13.440 --> 40:16.560
And I want to rule the Emerald City.

40:16.560 --> 40:18.160
Says the scarecrow.

40:18.160 --> 40:19.960
I have a kind heart.

40:19.960 --> 40:21.200
Says the Tin Woodman.

40:21.200 --> 40:24.120
I want to rule the land of the Winkies

40:24.120 --> 40:27.480
because the Wicked Witch of the West is dead.

40:27.480 --> 40:29.880
I am a courageous lion.

40:29.880 --> 40:31.120
Says the lion.

40:31.120 --> 40:34.440
I want to be the king of the forest.

40:34.440 --> 40:35.280
Good.

40:35.280 --> 40:36.520
Says the good witch.

40:36.520 --> 40:39.480
You can all have what you want.

40:39.480 --> 40:42.480
This is a happy moment for everyone.

40:42.480 --> 40:47.560
Dorothy kisses the scarecrow, the Tin Woodman, and the lion.

40:47.560 --> 40:49.400
Goodbye, my dear friends.

40:49.400 --> 40:51.920
She says, goodbye, Dorothy.

40:51.920 --> 40:53.240
And thank you.

40:53.240 --> 40:58.720
Her friends say, she picks Toto up and closes her eyes.

40:58.720 --> 41:01.920
Then she clicks her heels three times and says,

41:01.920 --> 41:04.280
take me home to Kansas.

41:04.280 --> 41:06.640
Suddenly, there is a strong wind.

41:09.440 --> 41:12.520
It blows her and Toto into the sky,

41:12.520 --> 41:13.960
and they fly and fly.

41:20.160 --> 41:26.440
MUSIC

41:26.440 --> 41:29.120
Finally, they are on the ground.

41:29.120 --> 41:33.120
Dorothy opens her eyes and looks around.

41:33.120 --> 41:35.840
They are in Kansas.

41:35.840 --> 41:40.280
She looks at her feet, but her magic shoes aren't there.

41:40.280 --> 41:43.160
Then she sees Aunt M and Uncle Henry.

41:43.160 --> 41:44.560
I'm home again.

41:44.560 --> 41:46.520
Aunt M and Uncle Henry.

41:46.520 --> 41:48.280
I'm so happy.

41:48.280 --> 41:49.520
She cries.

42:09.840 --> 42:10.920
MUSIC

42:10.920 --> 42:12.880
Listening activity.

42:12.880 --> 42:14.880
One.

42:15.760 --> 42:17.880
These people are very short.

42:17.880 --> 42:19.280
They are very friendly.

42:19.280 --> 42:22.880
And now, they are very happy because the wicked witch

42:22.880 --> 42:24.920
of the east is dead.

42:24.920 --> 42:26.840
They live near the yellow brick road.

42:29.520 --> 42:31.520
Two.

42:31.520 --> 42:33.280
This thing is magic.

42:33.280 --> 42:37.040
When I blow it, it calls the winged monkeys.

42:37.040 --> 42:39.480
They then do anything you want them to do.

42:42.080 --> 42:42.600
Three.

42:45.040 --> 42:48.120
This is one of the wizard's magic tricks.

42:48.120 --> 42:50.800
It's like a big round paper ball.

42:50.800 --> 42:54.000
It has eyes, a mouth, and a nose.

42:54.000 --> 42:55.560
It also talks.

42:57.720 --> 42:58.720
Four.

42:59.880 --> 43:02.400
These are very special.

43:02.400 --> 43:05.600
For your dream to come true, you must click your heels

43:05.600 --> 43:08.320
three times and say what you want.

43:08.320 --> 43:09.520
They're magic.

